Description: The magical beast Ten Tails has awoken and only Naruto and the Allied Shinobi Forces stand in its way!
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 65
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and helps usher them safely into the afterlife. In this volume, Ichigo returns to the World of the Living, where he encounters his father.
Title: BLEACH, VOL. 60
Author: Tite Kubo

Description: Death the Kid decides that the only way to ensure harmony and balance is to destroy civilization until nothing remains.
Title: SOUL EATER, VOL. 19
Author: Atsushi Ohkubo

Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: In the not–too–distant future, a popular virtual reality video game traps its users, so the only way to log out is to beat the game. But if they die in the virtual world, it also means “game over” in the real world!
Title: SWORD ART ONLINE: AINCRAD
Author: Reki Kawahara and Tamako Nakamura
Contributor: by Reki Kawahara and Tamako Nakamura

Description: In this prequel story, a group of Titan–worshipping cultists open the gates and a baby is the only survivor when a Titan inevitably attacks.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: BEFORE THE FALL, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama, Ryo Suzukaze and Satoshi Shiki
Contributor: by Hajime Isayama, Ryo Suzukaze and Satoshi Shiki

Description: Fairy Tail vaults to the top of the rankings in the Grand Magic Games but why aren’t they excited about their victory?
Title: FAIRY TAIL, VOL. 36
Author: Hiro Mashima

Description: Two magical girls, Mami and Kyouko Sakura, join forces and become fast friends until a decision from Kyouko’s past comes back to haunt her.
Title: PUELLA MAGI MADOKA MAGICA: THE DIFFERENT STORY, VOL. 1
Author: Magica Quartet and Hanokage

Description: Hana meets and falls in love with a man who is a werewolf, but when tragedy strikes, she is forced to raise their children alone in this adaptation of the animated film.
Title: WOLF CHILDREN: AME AND YUKI
Author: Mamoru Hosoda and Yu

Description: This spin-off series features the middle school adventures of Eren, Mikasa and the rest of the “Attack On Titan” cast.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: JUNIOR HIGH, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama and Saki Nakagawa
Contributor: by Hajime Isayama and Saki Nakagawa
